		<hr size="1">Ratio is conventionally primary in offhand - there is, however, a case to be made that speed is relevant, as more hits = more taunt, but a good ratio weapon with a nice aggro proc (like a Frostbringer) is the best choice, IMAO.  </P><P>Based strictly on ratio, the Centi is about 9% better than the lamentation nominally, so maybe 2-3% overall (assuming offhand damage is around 1/4 to 1/3 of total).  500 PP isn't a life altering amount, nor is the damage a big differential.  So, you're right, but it's not a big enough difference to really matter.</P><P><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=29717">Nephtu Morgulduin</A>  Dark Elf Revenant &<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=32033">Japakazol Garasjulioson</A>  Halfling Warlord of<BR>Twilight Requiem - Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
