		<hr size="1">Warriors that use dual Lammies generally don't understand the mechanics of melee combat, and they use them because either a) they look cool dual-wielding the same weapon or b) everyone else uses Lammies, so they must be cool, so I'll get two.</P><P>The sole case for putting a Lammy in your off hand is because of it's 19 delay, but since your off hand isn't going to be hitting very often anyway, the additional taunt generated by those extra swings is going to be fairly minimal, IMO.</P><P>It's not proof, because as far as I know, no one actually knows the maths that go into making up the hate list, but I'd bet you generate more aggro with the higher damage, slower Centi LS in your off hand than you do with the Lammy. With no off-hand bonus, a 9 dmg weapon is pretty weak.</P><P>I think your friend is wrong.. *shrug*</P><P>--<BR>Rafal B'Fereign, Bard of the 30th Song<BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78104" target=_new">Tarsk Longstrider</a>, Champion of the Wolves o' the North<BR>Xev</P><P>"Okay. We got enough youth. How about a fountain of SMART?"<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
