		<hr size="1">Here is my thoughts on this...</P><P>Your offhand swinging is independent of your main hand.  The offhand uses your dual wield skill and the delay of the offhand weapon to decide weather or not your swing.</P><P>Now for my assumption...</P><P>I assume that the system checks to see if the weapon has recycled yet, and then checks the dual wield skill.  If both are successful, then you swing with your offhand.</P><P>If it checks the DW skill first, then it is imposing an inherent delay on the weapon that is based on your DW skill and not the weapons delay.</P><P>Working with my assumption, a faster offhand weapon would check DW more often (in theory, would succeed the same percentage of time).  Checking DW more often would mean you swing more often; therefore, generating more aggro.</P><P>In the grand scheme of things, does a 19 delay weapon in the offhand swing that much more than a 24 delay weapon?  Probably not.</P><P>In terms of aggro from the offhand, I think the faster of the two offhand weapons (with similar ratios) would generate more aggro.</P><P>In terms of damage, if the weapons have the same ratio, then the two weapons would generate similar damage.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
